{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851039439,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f85c6400156FRi3jQATZ617","messageID":"msg_d78f8534d001NBPRrimREkql5H","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-004  \n6: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Establish the HTTP service framework for the WorkloadManager component, providing RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, health endpoints, and integration with the Kubernetes client-go library.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: HTTP Server Bootstrap\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a configurable HTTP server that can be started and gracefully shut down.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Server starts with configuration\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid server configuration with host, port, and handler registrations\n22: - **WHEN** the operator calls `server.Start()`\n23: - **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL bind to the configured address and begin accepting connections\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Server shuts down gracefully\n26: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active connections\n27: - **WHEN** the operator calls `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with a context timeout\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL stop accepting new connections, wait for existing requests to complete (within timeout), and release resources\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Server configuration from environment\n31: - **GIVEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST` (default \"0.0.0.0\") and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` (default \"8080\")\n32: - **WHEN** the operator initializes the server configuration\n33: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL read from these environment variables with sensible defaults\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Server supports TLS configuration\n36: - **GIVEN** TLS certificate and key files specified in configuration\n37: - **WHEN** the operator starts the server with TLS enabled\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL serve HTTPS using the provided certificates\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: Health and Readiness Endpoints\n43: \n44: The system SHALL expose standard Kubernetes health check endpoints for liveness and readiness probes.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Liveness endpoint returns healthy\n47: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager HTTP server is running\n48: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/healthz`\n49: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with body `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` when the process is alive\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Readiness endpoint reflects dependency health\n52: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager has initialized all dependencies (Kubernetes client, Redis connection)\n53: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/readyz`\n54: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with body `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` when all dependencies are healthy\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Readiness endpoint returns not ready\n57: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager has a failed dependency (e.g., Kubernetes API unreachable)\n58: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/readyz`\n59: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 503 with body `{\"status\": \"not_ready\", \"reason\": \"<failure_reason>\"}`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Health endpoint includes detailed checks\n62: - **GIVEN** the configuration enables verbose health checks\n63: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/healthz?verbose=true`\n64: - **THEN** the server SHALL return detailed health status for each registered health check component\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: RESTful API for AgentRuntime Resources\n69: \n70: The system SHALL expose RESTful HTTP endpoints for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime resources.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes\n73: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace `default`\n74: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n75: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with a JSON list of AgentRuntime objects\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Get single AgentRuntime\n78: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n79: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n80: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with the AgentRuntime JSON object\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Get non-existent AgentRuntime returns 404\n83: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `non-existent` exists in namespace `default`\n84: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/non-existent`\n85: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with error details\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime\n88: - **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime JSON payload\n89: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with the payload\n90: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the resource via Kubernetes API and return HTTP 201 with the created object\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Create invalid AgentRuntime returns 400\n93: - **GIVEN** an invalid AgentRuntime JSON payload (missing required fields)\n94: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with the invalid payload\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with validation error details\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime\n98: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n99: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated spec\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the resource and return HTTP 200 with the updated object\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n103: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n104: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n105: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the resource and return HTTP 200 with the deleted object\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntimes\n108: - **GIVEN** the server supports streaming endpoints\n109: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL establish a streaming connection and emit ADDED/MODIFIED/DELETED events as resources change\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: RESTful API for CodeInterpreter Resources\n115: \n116: The system SHALL expose RESTful HTTP endpoints for CRUD operations on CodeInterpreter resources.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: List CodeInterpreters\n119: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace `default`\n120: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n121: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with a JSON list of CodeInterpreter objects\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Get single CodeInterpreter\n124: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default`\n125: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n126: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with the CodeInterpreter JSON object\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter\n129: - **GIVEN** a valid CodeInterpreter JSON payload\n130: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with the payload\n131: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the resource via Kubernetes API and return HTTP 201 with the created object\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter\n134: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter`\n135: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter` with updated spec\n136: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the resource and return HTTP 200 with the updated object\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n139: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter`\n140: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n141: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the resource and return HTTP 200 with the deleted object\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreters\n144: - **GIVEN** the server supports streaming endpoints\n145: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n146: - **THEN** the server SHALL establish a streaming connection and emit ADDED/MODIFIED/DELETED events as resources change\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Resource Status Endpoints\n151: \n152: The system SHALL expose endpoints for retrieving and updating resource status.\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime status\n155: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists with status information\n156: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n157: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with only the status portion of the resource\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n160: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n161: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with new status\n162: - **THEN** the server SHALL update only the status subresource and return HTTP 200\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Get CodeInterpreter status\n165: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists with status information\n166: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter/status`\n167: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with only the status portion of the resource\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Client Integration\n172: \n173: The system SHALL integrate with the Kubernetes API using the generated client-go library.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Client initialization from in-cluster config\n176: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n177: - **WHEN** the server initializes the Kubernetes client\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL use in-cluster configuration to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n181: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n182: - **WHEN** the server initializes the Kubernetes client\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Client uses typed clientset\n186: - **GIVEN** the Kubernetes client is initialized\n187: - **WHEN** the server handles AgentRuntime API requests\n188: - **THEN** it SHALL use the generated `clientset.Interface` from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Client handles authentication\n191: - **GIVEN** the service account has proper RBAC permissions\n192: - **WHEN** the server makes API requests\n193: - **THEN** the client SHALL authenticate using the service account token and certificate\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: Request Routing and Middleware\n198: \n199: The system SHALL implement HTTP request routing with middleware support for cross-cutting concerns.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Route registration\n202: - **GIVEN** the server is being configured\n203: - **WHEN** handlers are registered with the router\n204: - **THEN** each route SHALL be mapped to the correct HTTP method and path pattern\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Request logging middleware\n207: - **GIVEN** a request is received by the server\n208: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n209: - **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and duration\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Request ID middleware\n212: - **GIVEN** a request is received without an `X-Request-ID` header\n213: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n214: - **THEN** the server SHALL generate a unique request ID and include it in response headers\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: CORS middleware\n217: - **GIVEN** CORS is enabled in configuration\n218: - **WHEN** a cross-origin request is received\n219: - **THEN** the server SHALL respond with appropriate CORS headers\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Panic recovery middleware\n222: - **GIVEN** a request handler panics during execution\n223: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n224: - **THEN** the server SHALL recover from the panic, log the error, and return HTTP 500 without crashing\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Authentication middleware\n227: - **GIVEN** authentication is enabled in configuration\n228: - **WHEN** a request is received without valid credentials\n229: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Request/Response Serialization\n234: \n235: The system SHALL properly serialize and deserialize JSON request and response bodies.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: JSON request deserialization\n238: - **GIVEN** a POST request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n239: - **WHEN** the server receives the request body\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL deserialize the JSON into the appropriate Go struct\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: JSON response serialization\n243: - **GIVEN** a handler returns a Go struct\n244: - **WHEN** the server sends the response\n245: - **THEN** it SHALL serialize the struct to JSON with `Content-Type: application/json`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: JSON field naming convention\n248: - **GIVEN** API response structs use camelCase JSON tags\n249: - **WHEN** responses are serialized\n250: - **THEN** field names SHALL follow camelCase convention (e.g., `createdAt`, `resourceVersion`)\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Error response format\n253: - **GIVEN** an error occurs during request processing\n254: - **WHEN** the server returns an error response\n255: - **THEN** it SHALL return a JSON object with `error` and `message` fields (e.g., `{\"error\": \"NotFound\", \"message\": \"resource not found\"}`)\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Query Parameter Support\n260: \n261: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes-style query parameters for list operations.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Label selector filtering\n264: - **GIVEN** resources with various labels exist\n265: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?labelSelector=app=myapp`\n266: - **THEN** the server SHALL return only resources matching the label selector\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Field selector filtering\n269: - **GIVEN** resources with various field values exist\n270: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?fieldSelector=spec.image=myimage`\n271: - **THEN** the server SHALL return only resources matching the field selector\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Pagination with limit and continue\n274: - **GIVEN** more than 100 resources exist\n275: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?limit=10`\n276: - **THEN** the server SHALL return at most 10 items and include a `continue` token for pagination\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Watch with resource version\n279: - **GIVEN** resources exist at resource version `12345`\n280: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?watch=true&resourceVersion=12345`\n281: - **THEN** the server SHALL start the watch from that resource version\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n286: \n287: The system SHALL expose Prometheus metrics for monitoring HTTP server performance.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: HTTP request metrics\n290: - **GIVEN** the server is handling requests\n291: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `http_requests_total` counter with labels for method, path, and status\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: HTTP request duration metrics\n295: - **GIVEN** the server is handling requests\n296: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `http_request_duration_seconds` histogram with labels for method and path\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Kubernetes client metrics\n300: - **GIVEN** the server is making Kubernetes API calls\n301: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `kubernetes_client_requests_total` counter for API operations\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Resource operation metrics\n305: - **GIVEN** the server is processing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter operations\n306: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL expose counters for create/update/delete operations by resource type\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Structured Logging\n312: \n313: The system SHALL implement structured logging for all operations.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Request logging with fields\n316: - **GIVEN** a request is processed\n317: - **WHEN** the server logs the request\n318: - **THEN** it SHALL include structured fields: `method`, `path`, `status`, `duration`, `request_id`\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Error logging with context\n321: - **GIVEN** an error occurs during API processing\n322: - **WHEN** the error is logged\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL include structured fields: `error`, `resource_type`, `resource_name`, `namespace`, `request_id`\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API logging\n326: - **GIVEN** the server makes a Kubernetes API call\n327: - **WHEN** the operation is logged\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL include fields: `operation`, `resource`, `namespace`, `duration`, `error` (if any)\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Configurable log level\n331: - **GIVEN** the `LOG_LEVEL` environment variable is set to `debug`\n332: - **WHEN** the server logs messages\n333: - **THEN** debug-level messages SHALL be output alongside info and error messages\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: Configuration Management\n338: \n339: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables and configuration files.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Server configuration from environment variables\n342: - **GIVEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_TLS_CERT`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_TLS_KEY`\n343: - **WHEN** the configuration is loaded\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL populate the server configuration struct with these values\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Kubernetes configuration from environment\n347: - **GIVEN** environment variables `KUBECONFIG` or in-cluster configuration\n348: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes client configuration is loaded\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL use the specified kubeconfig or in-cluster settings\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Redis configuration from environment\n352: - **GIVEN** environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n353: - **WHEN** the Redis client configuration is loaded\n354: - **THEN** it SHALL populate the Redis connection configuration\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Configuration validation\n357: - **GIVEN** an invalid configuration (e.g., invalid port number)\n358: - **WHEN** the configuration is loaded\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error before starting the server\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n364: \n365: The system SHALL implement consistent error handling across all endpoints.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API errors mapped to HTTP status\n368: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsNotFound`\n369: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n370: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API conflict mapped to HTTP 409\n373: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsConflict`\n374: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n375: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 409 Conflict\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API unauthorized mapped to HTTP 403\n378: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsForbidden`\n379: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n380: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Internal server errors mapped to HTTP 500\n383: - **GIVEN** an unexpected internal error occurs\n384: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n385: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with a generic error message (details logged but not exposed)\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Validation errors mapped to HTTP 400\n388: - **GIVEN** a request fails validation\n389: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n390: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with validation error details\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Server Command Line Interface\n395: \n396: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for starting the WorkloadManager server.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Server starts with default configuration\n399: - **GIVEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is built\n400: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server`\n401: - **THEN** the server SHALL start with default configuration values\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Server starts with flags\n404: - **GIVEN** command-line flags `--host=0.0.0.0 --port=9090 --tls-cert=/cert.pem --tls-key=/key.pem`\n405: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server` with these flags\n406: - **THEN** the server SHALL start with the specified configuration\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Server shows help\n409: - **GIVEN** the operator wants to see available options\n410: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server --help`\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL display help text with all available flags and their descriptions\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Server respects signal handling\n414: - **GIVEN** the server is running\n415: - **WHEN** the process receives SIGTERM or SIGINT\n416: - **THEN** the server SHALL initiate graceful shutdown with a configurable timeout\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## File Index\n421: \n422: | Path | Purpose |\n423: |------|---------|\n424: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Main entry point for the WorkloadManager binary |\n425: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go` | HTTP server bootstrap and lifecycle management |\n426: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/config.go` | Server configuration structures and loading |\n427: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/routes.go` | HTTP route definitions and handler registration |\n428: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware implementations (logging, recovery, auth) |\n429: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | Health and readiness endpoint handlers |\n430: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime CRUD endpoint handlers |\n431: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter CRUD endpoint handlers |\n432: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/common.go` | Common handler utilities and response helpers |\n433: | `pkg/workloadmanager/client/kube.go` | Kubernetes client initialization and wrapper |\n434: | `pkg/workloadmanager/metrics/metrics.go` | Prometheus metrics definitions and recording |\n435: | `pkg/workloadmanager/logger/logger.go` | Structured logging configuration and helpers |\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## Dependencies\n440: \n441: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n442: |------------|---------|---------|\n443: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset |\n444: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes REST client |\n445: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n446: | `github.com/gorilla/mux` or `net/http` | Latest | HTTP routing |\n447: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Prometheus metrics |\n448: | `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` or `slog` | Latest | Structured logging |\n449: | `github.com/rs/cors` | Latest | CORS middleware (optional) |\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ## API Endpoints Summary\n454: \n455: | Method | Path | Description |\n456: |--------|------|-------------|\n457: | GET | `/healthz` | Liveness probe |\n458: | GET | `/readyz` | Readiness probe |\n459: | GET | `/metrics` | Prometheus metrics |\n460: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n461: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n462: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n463: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update AgentRuntime |\n464: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n465: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get AgentRuntime status |\n466: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Update AgentRuntime status |\n467: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n468: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n469: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n470: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n471: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n472: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get CodeInterpreter status |\n473: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update CodeInterpreter status |\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ## Notes\n478: \n479: - The WorkloadManager HTTP service serves as the control plane API for the AgentCube system\n480: - All endpoints that modify resources SHALL use the Kubernetes API server for persistence\n481: - The service SHALL be stateless, with all state stored in Kubernetes resources and Redis\n482: - The API follows RESTful conventions similar to the Kubernetes API for consistency\n483: - WebSocket or Server-Sent Events (SSE) may be used for the watch endpoints\n484: - The service SHALL support both in-cluster and external Kubernetes cluster configurations\n\n(End of file - total 484 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-004  \n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nEstablish the HTTP service framework for the WorkloadManager component, providing RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, health endpoints, and integration with the Kubernetes client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Server Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a configurable HTTP server that can be started and gracefully shut down.\n\n#### Scenario: Server starts with configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851039412,"end":1775851039437}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851039452,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f865e3001UcMRD4B81he0xZ","messageID":"msg_d78f8534d001NBPRrimREkql5H","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type ProtocolType string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n31: \tProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n32: \n33: \t// ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n34: \tProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n35: )\n36: \n37: // AuthModeType represents the authentication mode for the CodeInterpreter.\n38: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n39: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n40: type AuthModeType string\n41: \n42: const (\n43: \t// AuthModePicoD represents authentication using PicoD.\n44: \tAuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n45: \n46: \t// AuthModeNone represents no authentication.\n47: \tAuthModeNone AuthModeType = \"none\"\n48: )\n49: \n50: // TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n51: // This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\n52: type TargetPort struct {\n53: \t// PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n54: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n55: \tPathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n56: \n57: \t// Name is an optional name for this port.\n58: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n59: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n60: \n61: \t// Port is the port number to expose.\n62: \t// This field is required.\n63: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n64: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n65: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n66: \tPort uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n67: \n68: \t// Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n69: \t// Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n70: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n72: \tProtocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: // CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a CodeInterpreter sandbox.\n76: // It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n77: type CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n78: \t// Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n79: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n80: \t// +mapType=atomic\n81: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n82: \n83: \t// Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n84: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n85: \t// +mapType=atomic\n86: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n87: \n88: \t// Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n89: \t// This field is required.\n90: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n91: \tSpec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n92: }\n93: \n94: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n95: // This specification describes the configuration for a code interpreter sandbox instance\n96: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n97: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \t// +listType=map\n100: \t// +listMapKey=port\n101: \tPorts []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n102: \n103: \t// Template is the sandbox template containing the pod specification.\n104: \t// This field is required.\n105: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n106: \tTemplate *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n107: \n108: \t// SessionTimeout specifies the session timeout duration.\n109: \t// Defaults to \"15m\" if not specified.\n110: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n111: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n112: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// MaxSessionDuration specifies the maximum session duration.\n115: \t// Defaults to \"8h\" if not specified.\n116: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n117: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n118: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n119: \n120: \t// WarmPoolSize specifies the number of warm sandbox instances to maintain.\n121: \t// If not specified, no warm pool is maintained.\n122: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n123: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n124: \tWarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// AuthMode specifies the authentication mode for the sandbox.\n127: \t// Defaults to \"picod\" if not specified.\n128: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n129: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"picod\"\n130: \tAuthMode AuthModeType `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n131: }\n132: \n133: // CodeInterpreterConditionType represents a condition type for CodeInterpreter.\n134: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n135: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n136: type CodeInterpreterConditionType string\n137: \n138: const (\n139: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionReady indicates the CodeInterpreter is ready to accept requests.\n140: \tCodeInterpreterConditionReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Ready\"\n141: \n142: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n143: \tCodeInterpreterConditionSandboxCreated CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n144: \n145: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n146: \tCodeInterpreterConditionSandboxReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n147: \n148: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionFailed indicates the CodeInterpreter has failed.\n149: \tCodeInterpreterConditionFailed CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Failed\"\n150: )\n151: \n152: // CodeInterpreterCondition represents a condition of a CodeInterpreter.\n153: type CodeInterpreterCondition struct {\n154: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n156: \tType CodeInterpreterConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n157: \n158: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n159: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n160: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n161: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n162: \n163: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n164: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n165: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n166: \n167: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n174: }\n175: \n176: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n177: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n178: // state of the sandbox instance.\n179: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n180: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \t// +listType=map\n183: \t// +listMapKey=type\n184: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n185: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n186: \tConditions []CodeInterpreterCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// Ready indicates whether the CodeInterpreter is ready to accept requests.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tReady *bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n191: }\n192: \n193: // +genclient\n194: // +genclient:noStatus\n195: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n196: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n197: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n198: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n199: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n200: \n201: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n202: // A CodeInterpreter represents a sandbox instance for running code interpretation workloads.\n203: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n204: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n205: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n206: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n207: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n208: \n209: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the CodeInterpreter.\n210: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n211: \tSpec CodeInterpreterSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n212: \n213: \t// Status defines the observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n214: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n215: \tStatus CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n216: }\n217: \n218: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n219: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n220: \n221: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n222: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n223: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n224: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n225: \n226: \t// Items is the list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n227: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n228: \tItems []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n229: }\n\n(End of file - total 229 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go","time":{"start":1775851039417,"end":1775851039450}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851039455,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f860da0010g9qXz1uVMNW28","messageID":"msg_d78f8534d001NBPRrimREkql5H","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // AgentRuntimePhase represents the current phase of an AgentRuntime.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// AgentRuntimePhasePending indicates the sandbox is being created.\n31: \tAgentRuntimePhasePending AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n32: \n33: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n34: \tAgentRuntimePhaseRunning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n35: \n36: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n37: \tAgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded AgentRuntimePhase = \"Succeeded\"\n38: \n39: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n40: \tAgentRuntimePhaseFailed AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n41: \n42: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n43: \tAgentRuntimePhaseUnknown AgentRuntimePhase = \"Unknown\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: // AgentRuntimeConditionType represents a condition type for AgentRuntime.\n47: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n48: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n49: type AgentRuntimeConditionType string\n50: \n51: const (\n52: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionReady indicates the AgentRuntime is ready to accept requests.\n53: \tAgentRuntimeConditionReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Ready\"\n54: \n55: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n56: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n57: \n58: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n59: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n60: \n61: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionFailed indicates the AgentRuntime has failed.\n62: \tAgentRuntimeConditionFailed AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Failed\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n66: // This specification describes the configuration for a sandbox instance\n67: // that will run an AI agent.\n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69: \t// Image is the container image to use for the sandbox.\n70: \t// This field is required and must be a valid container image reference.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n72: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n73: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n74: \n75: \t// Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n76: \t// If not specified, default resource limits will be applied.\n77: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n78: \tResources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n81: \t// These variables will be available to the running agent.\n82: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n83: \t// +listType=map\n84: \t// +listMapKey=name\n85: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n86: \n87: \t// Command overrides the default container entrypoint.\n88: \t// If not specified, the image's default entrypoint will be used.\n89: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n90: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n91: \n92: \t// Args provides arguments to the command or the default entrypoint.\n93: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n94: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n95: \n96: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory for the container.\n97: \t// If not specified, the container's default working directory will be used.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n100: \n101: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n102: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n103: \t// +listType=map\n104: \t// +listMapKey=containerPort\n105: \tPorts []corev1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n106: \n107: \t// VolumeMounts defines volumes to mount into the sandbox container.\n108: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n109: \t// +listType=map\n110: \t// +listMapKey=name\n111: \tVolumeMounts []corev1.VolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n112: \n113: \t// Volumes defines the volumes that can be mounted by the sandbox.\n114: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n115: \t// +listType=map\n116: \t// +listMapKey=name\n117: \tVolumes []corev1.Volume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n118: \n119: \t// ServiceAccountName specifies the service account to use for the sandbox pod.\n120: \t// If not specified, the default service account will be used.\n121: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n122: \tServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n123: \n124: \t// NodeSelector specifies node labels for pod scheduling.\n125: \t// The pod will only be scheduled on nodes matching these labels.\n126: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n127: \t// +mapType=atomic\n128: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// Tolerations allow the pod to be scheduled on nodes with matching taints.\n131: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n132: \t// +listType=atomic\n133: \tTolerations []corev1.Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n134: \n135: \t// Affinity defines the scheduling constraints for the pod.\n136: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n137: \tAffinity *corev1.Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n138: \n139: \t// TTLSecondsAfterFinished specifies the time to live (in seconds) after\n140: \t// the sandbox has finished (succeeded or failed). The sandbox will be\n141: \t// automatically deleted after this time.\n142: \t// If not specified, the sandbox will not be automatically deleted.\n143: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n144: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n145: \tTTLSecondsAfterFinished *int32 `json:\"ttlSecondsAfterFinished,omitempty\"`\n146: \n147: \t// IdleTimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum time (in seconds) the sandbox\n148: \t// can be idle before being terminated. If not specified, no idle timeout\n149: \t// is enforced.\n150: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n151: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n152: \tIdleTimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"idleTimeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// MaxLifetimeSeconds specifies the maximum lifetime (in seconds) of the sandbox.\n155: \t// The sandbox will be terminated after this duration regardless of activity.\n156: \t// If not specified, no maximum lifetime is enforced.\n157: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n158: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n159: \tMaxLifetimeSeconds *int32 `json:\"maxLifetimeSeconds,omitempty\"`\n160: }\n161: \n162: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n163: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n164: // state of the sandbox instance.\n165: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n166: \t// Phase represents the current phase of the AgentRuntime.\n167: \t// Possible values: Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tPhase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's state.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \t// +listType=map\n174: \t// +listMapKey=type\n175: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n176: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n177: \tConditions []AgentRuntimeCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n178: \n179: \t// SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n180: \t// This is set once the sandbox pod has been successfully created.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// PodName is the name of the pod running the sandbox.\n185: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n186: \tPodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// PodIP is the IP address assigned to the sandbox pod.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tPodIP string `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// StartTime is the time when the sandbox was started.\n193: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n194: \tStartTime *metav1.Time `json:\"startTime,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// CompletionTime is the time when the sandbox completed (succeeded or failed).\n197: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n198: \tCompletionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"completionTime,omitempty\"`\n199: \n200: \t// LastActivityTime is the time of the last activity in the sandbox.\n201: \t// Used for idle timeout tracking.\n202: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n203: \tLastActivityTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastActivityTime,omitempty\"`\n204: \n205: \t// Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n206: \t// This may contain error messages or other status information.\n207: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n208: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n209: \n210: \t// Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n211: \t// This is typically a CamelCase string indicating why the phase is set.\n212: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n213: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n214: \n215: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n216: \t// This is used to determine if the spec has been processed.\n217: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n218: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n219: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // AgentRuntimeCondition represents a condition of an AgentRuntime.\n223: type AgentRuntimeCondition struct {\n224: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n225: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n226: \tType AgentRuntimeConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n227: \n228: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n229: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n230: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n231: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n232: \n233: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n234: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n235: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n236: \n237: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n238: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n239: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n242: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n243: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n244: }\n245: \n246: // +genclient\n247: // +genclient:noStatus\n248: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n249: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n250: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=agentruntimes,shortName=ar;ars,singular=agentruntime,categories={agentcube,all}\n251: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n252: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase of the agent runtime\"\n253: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Sandbox\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.sandboxId`,description=\"ID of the sandbox pod\"\n254: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n255: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Message\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.message`,priority=1\n256: \n257: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n258: // An AgentRuntime represents a sandbox instance for running AI agents.\n259: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n260: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n261: type AgentRuntime struct {\n262: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n263: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n264: \n265: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the AgentRuntime.\n266: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n267: \tSpec AgentRuntimeSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n268: \n269: \t// Status defines the observed state of the AgentRuntime.\n270: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n271: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n272: }\n273: \n274: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n275: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n276: \n277: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime resources.\n278: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n279: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n280: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n281: \n282: \t// Items is the list of AgentRuntime resources.\n283: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n284: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n285: }\n\n(End of file - total 285 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go","time":{"start":1775851039415,"end":1775851039453}}}}
