{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851063471,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8af61001Pvg4lZkrLpFb2C","messageID":"msg_d78f88d2e001ioUpSjRQWD8sZB","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Design: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-007  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Large  \n9: \n10: The K8s Reconciler Controller provides event-driven reconciliation for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the AgentCube system. It uses controller-runtime to watch resources, manage lifecycle transitions, and ensure cluster state matches desired state.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                     Kubernetes API Server                                   │\n21: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n22: │  │                     CRD Resources                                     │  │\n23: │  │  ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐                     │  │\n24: │  │  │ AgentRuntime       │  │ CodeInterpreter    │                     │  │\n25: │  │  │ (watch)            │  │ (watch)            │                     │  │\n26: │  │  └────────┬───────────┘  └────────┬───────────┘                     │  │\n27: │  └───────────┼───────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────┘  │\n28: │              │                       │                                       │\n29: └──────────────┼───────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┘\n30:                │                       │\n31:                ▼                       ▼\n32: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n33: │                     Reconciler Controller                                   │\n34: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n35: │  │                    Controller Manager                                   │ │\n36: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n37: │  │  │                      Source (Watches)                             │ │ │\n38: │  │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐              │ │ │\n39: │  │  │  │ AgentRuntime Source │  │ CodeInterpreter Src │              │ │ │\n40: │  │  │  │ · Create Events     │  │ · Create Events     │              │ │ │\n41: │  │  │  │ · Update Events     │  │ · Update Events     │              │ │ │\n42: │  │  │  │ · Delete Events     │  │ · Delete Events     │              │ │ │\n43: │  │  │  └──────────┬──────────┘  └──────────┬──────────┘              │ │ │\n44: │  │  └─────────────┼────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┘ │ │\n45: │  │                │                        │                           │ │\n46: │  │  ┌─────────────▼────────────────────────▼───────────────────────────┐ │ │\n47: │  │  │                      Work Queue                                   │ │ │\n48: │  │  │  · Rate limiting                                                   │ │ │\n49: │  │  │  · Retry with exponential backoff                                 │ │ │\n50: │  │  └────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n51: │  │                               │                                       │ │\n52: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n53: │  │  │                   Reconcile Loop                                  │ │ │\n54: │  │  │  ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐                │ │ │\n55: │  │  │  │ AgentRuntime       │  │ CodeInterpreter    │                │ │ │\n56: │  │  │  │ Reconciler         │  │ Reconciler         │                │ │ │\n57: │  │  │  └────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘                │ │ │\n58: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n59: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Components\n66: \n67: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## Interfaces\n72: \n73: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Data Flow\n78: \n79: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Error Handling\n84: \n85: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Testing Strategy\n90: \n91: ### TBD - To be detailed during implementation\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## References\n96: \n97: - [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime)\n98: - [AR-003: client-go Generated Code](../AR-003/)\n99: - [AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework](../AR-004/)\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Design: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Large  \n\nThe K8s Reconciler Controller provides event-driven reconciliation for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the AgentCube system. It uses controller-runtime to watch resources, manage lifecycle transitions, and ensure cluster state matches desired state.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Kubernetes API Server                                   │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775851063450,"end":1775851063469}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851063472,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8b477001SVII5KdpIWj5ne","messageID":"msg_d78f88d2e001ioUpSjRQWD8sZB","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-007\n2: title: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n3: module: pkg/workloadmanager\n4: language: Go\n5: size: L\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n9: # Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: L\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: reconciler-controller\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler controller for the WorkloadManager.\n23:     This controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles\n24:     their desired state with actual cluster state, and manages the lifecycle\n25:     of sandbox resources. It integrates with the controller-runtime framework\n26:     and provides event-driven reconciliation with proper error handling and\n27:     exponential backoff.\n28: \n29: # Scope\n30: scope:\n31:   in:\n32:     - CRD resource watchers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n33:     - Reconciliation loop implementation with controller-runtime\n34:     - Event-driven reconciliation on resource changes\n35:     - Exponential backoff for failed reconciliations\n36:     - Finalizer handling for graceful deletion\n37:     - Status updates and condition management\n38:     - OwnerReference management for garbage collection\n39:     - Integration with existing WorkloadManager service layer\n40:     - Reconcile queue with rate limiting\n41:     - Metrics and observability hooks\n42:   out:\n43:     - CRD type definitions (handled in AR-001/AR-002)\n44:     - client-go generated code (handled in AR-003)\n45:     - HTTP service framework (handled in AR-004)\n46:     - Sandbox creation/deletion logic (handled in AR-005/AR-006)\n47:     - Multi-cluster reconciliation (separate AR)\n48:     - Leader election for HA (separate AR)\n49: \n50: # Acceptance Criteria\n51: acceptance:\n52:   - Controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs\n53:   - Reconciliation loop processes create/update/delete events\n54:   - Exponential backoff for transient failures (configurable)\n55:   - Finalizers ensure graceful resource cleanup\n56:   - Status conditions accurately reflect resource state\n57:   - OwnerReferences are properly set for garbage collection\n58:   - Integration with WorkloadManager service layer\n59:   - Metrics exposed for reconciliation latency and errors\n60:   - Unit tests achieve >= 80% coverage\n61:   - Integration tests verify end-to-end reconciliation\n62: \n63: # References\n64: references:\n65:   - AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Types\n66:   - AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter Types\n67:   - AR-003: client-go Generated Code\n68:   - AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n69:   - AR-005: Sandbox Creation Handler\n70:   - AR-006: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n71: \n72: # Estimation\n73: estimation:\n74:   size: L\n75:   story_points: 8\n76:   days: 5\n\n(End of file - total 76 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-007\ntitle: K8s Reconciler 控制器\nmodule: pkg/workloadmanager\nlanguage: Go\nsize: L\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n# Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n# Language: Go\n# Size: L\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: reconciler-controller","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775851063455,"end":1775851063471}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851063476,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8bee00018FHd5jJ0s9Ycvu","messageID":"msg_d78f88d2e001ioUpSjRQWD8sZB","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-006  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management functionality for the WorkloadManager. This includes HTTP endpoints for deleting sandboxes (single, batch, force), graceful shutdown with configurable timeout, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan cleanup background workers. The implementation integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and extends the sandbox creation handler (AR-005).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Sandbox Single Deletion Endpoint\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to delete a single sandbox by its session ID.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Delete existing sandbox gracefully\n21: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-abc-123` exists in the Store\n22: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-abc-123`\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n24:   1. Extract the sessionID from the path parameter\n25:   2. Load the sandbox from Store by sessionID\n26:   3. Initiate graceful shutdown with default 30s timeout\n27:   4. Delete the underlying Sandbox/SandboxClaim CR via dynamic client\n28:   5. Delete the Store entry\n29:   6. Return HTTP 200 with `DeleteSandboxResponse` containing sandboxId and status \"deleted\"\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with custom graceful timeout\n32: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-def-456` exists\n33: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-def-456?gracefulTimeout=60s`\n34: - **THEN** the server SHALL use 60-second graceful shutdown timeout instead of default 30s\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent sandbox returns 404\n37: - **GIVEN** no sandbox with sessionID `sess-missing-789` exists in Store\n38: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-missing-789`\n39: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"Session ID sess-missing-789 not found, maybe already deleted\"\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox already being deleted returns 409\n42: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-deleting-000` is in \"terminating\" status\n43: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-deleting-000`\n44: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 409 with error code `DELETION_IN_PROGRESS`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox\n47: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox with sessionID `sess-ci-111` exists\n48: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/sess-ci-111`\n49: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the SandboxClaim (if warm pool) or Sandbox and return HTTP 200\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Sandbox Force Delete Endpoint\n54: \n55: The system SHALL support force deletion that bypasses graceful shutdown.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Force delete sandbox immediately\n58: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-stuck-222` exists and is stuck in terminating\n59: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/sandboxes/sess-stuck-222/terminate` or DELETE with `?force=true`\n60: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n61:   1. Skip graceful shutdown phase\n62:   2. Force delete the CR with grace period 0\n63:   3. Immediately delete the Store entry\n64:   4. Return HTTP 200 with status \"force-deleted\"\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Force delete with cascade\n67: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with dependent resources exists\n68: - **WHEN** a force delete is requested with `?force=true&orphanDependents=false`\n69: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete all dependent resources (pods, services) before deleting the sandbox\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ### Requirement: Sandbox Batch Deletion Endpoint\n74: \n75: The system SHALL support batch deletion of multiple sandboxes.\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Batch delete multiple sandboxes\n78: - **GIVEN** sandboxes with sessionIDs `[\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]` exist\n79: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/sandboxes` with body `{\"sessionIds\": [\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]}`\n80: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n81:   1. Validate all session IDs\n82:   2. Initiate deletion for all sandboxes in parallel\n83:   3. Return HTTP 200 with `BatchDeleteResponse` containing:\n84:      - `deleted`: list of successfully deleted sandbox IDs\n85:      - `failed`: list of failed deletions with error details\n86:      - `notFound`: list of session IDs not found\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Batch delete with partial failure\n89: - **GIVEN** sessionIDs `[\"sess-exists\", \"sess-missing\", \"sess-error\"]` where \"sess-missing\" doesn't exist and \"sess-error\" fails to delete\n90: - **WHEN** a batch delete is requested\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with partial results and details for each failure\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Batch delete with limit\n94: - **GIVEN** a request with more than 100 session IDs\n95: - **WHEN** validated\n96: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"batch size exceeds maximum of 100\"\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### Requirement: Graceful Shutdown Flow\n101: \n102: The system SHALL implement graceful shutdown with configurable timeout.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown succeeds within timeout\n105: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-grace-333` is running\n106: - **WHEN** delete is called with gracefulTimeout=30s\n107: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n108:   1. Set sandbox status to \"terminating\" in Store\n109:   2. Send graceful shutdown signal to sandbox pod\n110:   3. Wait for pod to terminate or timeout\n111:   4. If pod terminates within 30s, mark as \"deleted\"\n112:   5. Return success response\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown times out\n115: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod ignores shutdown signals\n116: - **WHEN** gracefulTimeout=30s elapses without pod termination\n117: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n118:   1. Force delete the pod with grace period 0\n119:   2. Log a warning about graceful shutdown timeout\n120:   3. Continue with resource cleanup\n121:   4. Return success with status \"deleted\" and warning flag\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Custom graceful timeout via query parameter\n124: - **GIVEN** a request with `?gracefulTimeout=120s`\n125: - **WHEN** processing the delete\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL wait up to 120 seconds for graceful shutdown\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Requirement: Resource Cleanup\n131: \n132: The system SHALL clean up all resources associated with a sandbox.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Cleanup sandbox resources\n135: - **GIVEN** a sandbox has associated Pod, Service, and Ingress resources\n136: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n138:   1. Delete the Sandbox/SandboxClaim CR\n139:   2. Delete all dependent pods\n140:   3. Delete associated services\n141:   4. Delete ingress rules (if any)\n142:   5. Update Store entry status to \"deleted\"\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Cleanup with owner references\n145: - **GIVEN** resources have owner references pointing to the Sandbox\n146: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is deleted with `propagationPolicy=Foreground`\n147: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL garbage collect all owned resources automatically\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store cleanup after resource deletion\n150: - **GIVEN** the Sandbox CR has been successfully deleted\n151: - **WHEN** resource cleanup completes\n152: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` to remove the Store entry\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Handle cleanup failure\n155: - **GIVEN** a resource deletion fails (e.g., API server error)\n156: - **WHEN** cleanup is attempted\n157: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n158:   1. Retry deletion up to 3 times with exponential backoff\n159:   2. If still failing, mark sandbox status as \"cleanup-failed\"\n160:   3. Return HTTP 500 with error code `CLEANUP_FAILED`\n161:   4. Background worker will retry cleanup later\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: Lifecycle State Management\n166: \n167: The system SHALL track and expose lifecycle states for sandboxes.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Get lifecycle state\n170: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-state-444` exists\n171: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/v1/sandboxes/sess-state-444/lifecycle`\n172: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with `LifecycleStateResponse` containing:\n173:   - Current state (running, idle, terminating, terminated, failed)\n174:   - State history\n175:   - Last transition time\n176:   - Reason for current state\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Lifecycle state transitions\n179: - **GIVEN** a sandbox transitions from \"running\" to \"terminating\" to \"terminated\"\n180: - **WHEN** state changes occur\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n182:   1. Update state in Store\n183:   2. Emit lifecycle event\n184:   3. Record transition timestamp and reason\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: List sandboxes by lifecycle state\n187: - **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes in various states\n188: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/v1/sandboxes?state=terminating`\n189: - **THEN** the server SHALL return only sandboxes in the \"terminating\" state\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Background Worker\n194: \n195: The system SHALL run a background worker to detect and auto-delete idle sandboxes.\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: Detect idle sandbox\n198: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `lastActivityTime` older than 15 minutes ago (configurable)\n199: - **WHEN** the idle detector scans (every 1 minute by default)\n200: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n201:   1. Identify sandbox as idle\n202:   2. Check grace period (5 minutes default) has passed\n203:   3. Initiate automatic deletion\n204:   4. Emit idle timeout event\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Activity resets idle timer\n207: - **GIVEN** a sandbox was marked for idle deletion\n208: - **WHEN** new activity updates `lastActivityTime` before deletion\n209: - **THEN** the system SHALL cancel the scheduled deletion and reset idle status\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Disable idle detection\n212: - **GIVEN** configuration `IDLE_DETECTION_ENABLED=false`\n213: - **WHEN** the system starts\n214: - **THEN** the idle detector SHALL NOT be started\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Configurable idle timeout\n217: - **GIVEN** environment variable `SANDBOX_IDLE_TIMEOUT=30m`\n218: - **WHEN** checking for idle sandboxes\n219: - **THEN** sandboxes idle for more than 30 minutes SHALL be marked for deletion\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ### Requirement: Orphan Cleanup Background Worker\n224: \n225: The system SHALL run a background worker to detect and clean up orphan resources.\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Detect orphan sandbox CR\n228: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR exists without a corresponding Store entry\n229: - **WHEN** the orphan detector scans (every 5 minutes by default)\n230: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n231:   1. Identify the CR as orphan\n232:   2. Check if CR is older than `ORPHAN_MAX_AGE` (1 hour default)\n233:   3. Delete the orphan CR\n234:   4. Log orphan cleanup event\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Detect zombie Store entry\n237: - **GIVEN** a Store entry exists for a deleted Sandbox CR\n238: - **WHEN** the orphan detector scans\n239: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n240:   1. Verify CR no longer exists in Kubernetes\n241:   2. Delete the stale Store entry\n242:   3. Log cleanup event\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Handle detection errors\n245: - **GIVEN** the orphan detector encounters an API error\n246: - **WHEN** scanning for orphans\n247: - **THEN** the system SHALL log the error and continue with next item (not crash)\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ### Requirement: Idempotency and Concurrency\n252: \n253: The system SHALL handle concurrent deletion requests safely.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Duplicate delete requests\n256: - **GIVEN** a delete request for sessionID `sess-dup-555` is in progress\n257: - **WHEN** another delete request arrives for the same sessionID\n258: - **THEN** the second request SHALL return HTTP 409 with `DELETION_IN_PROGRESS` error\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Retry after in-progress deletion completes\n261: - **GIVEN** a previous delete request completed successfully\n262: - **WHEN** another delete request arrives for the same sessionID\n263: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 (sandbox not found)\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Concurrent batch deletes\n266: - **GIVEN** two batch delete requests include overlapping session IDs\n267: - **WHEN** both requests are processed concurrently\n268: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n269:   1. Use distributed locking to prevent race conditions\n270:   2. Ensure each sandbox is deleted only once\n271:   3. Return appropriate results to both callers\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Error Handling and HTTP Status Mapping\n276: \n277: The system SHALL map internal errors to appropriate HTTP status codes.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Invalid session ID format\n280: - **GIVEN** a request with malformed session ID `sess-invalid-!!!`\n281: - **WHEN** the request is validated\n282: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"invalid session ID format\"\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API not found\n285: - **GIVEN** the Sandbox CR is not found in Kubernetes (but exists in Store)\n286: - **WHEN** attempting to delete\n287: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n288:   1. Treat as success (CR already deleted)\n289:   2. Clean up the Store entry\n290:   3. Return HTTP 200\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API conflict\n293: - **GIVEN** another process is modifying the Sandbox CR\n294: - **WHEN** attempting to delete\n295: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n296:   1. Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff\n297:   2. If still conflicting, return HTTP 409 with `CONFLICT` error code\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Store unavailable\n300: - **GIVEN** the Store (Redis) is unreachable\n301: - **WHEN** attempting to load or delete sandbox info\n302: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 503 with message \"store temporarily unavailable\"\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API unauthorized\n305: - **GIVEN** the service account lacks delete permissions\n306: - **WHEN** attempting to delete Sandbox CR\n307: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with message \"forbidden: insufficient permissions\"\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Request Validation\n312: \n313: The system SHALL validate all deletion requests.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Validate single delete request\n316: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`\n317: - **WHEN** the request is validated\n318: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n319:   1. Check sessionId is not empty\n320:   2. Verify sessionId format (UUID or alphanumeric)\n321:   3. Validate optional query parameters (gracefulTimeout, force, orphanDependents)\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Validate batch delete request\n324: - **GIVEN** a batch delete request with body\n325: - **WHEN** validated\n326: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n327:   1. Check sessionIds array is present and non-empty\n328:   2. Verify array length <= 100\n329:   3. Validate each sessionId format\n330:   4. Check for duplicate sessionIds\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Reject empty session ID\n333: - **GIVEN** a request with empty sessionId parameter\n334: - **WHEN** validated\n335: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"session ID is required\"\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ### Requirement: Authentication Integration\n340: \n341: The system SHALL integrate with authentication middleware when enabled.\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Delete with authentication enabled\n344: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and a valid bearer token in request\n345: - **WHEN** processing a delete request\n346: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n347:   1. Extract service account from auth context\n348:   2. Use per-user K8s client via `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()`\n349:   3. Verify user has RBAC permissions to delete Sandboxes in the namespace\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Reject delete without auth\n352: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and no Authorization header\n353: - **WHEN** the auth middleware processes the request\n354: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 before reaching the delete handler\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Delete with insufficient permissions\n357: - **GIVEN** a user with read-only access attempts to delete\n358: - **WHEN** the K8s delete call is made\n359: - **THEN** the Kubernetes API SHALL return 403 and the server SHALL propagate it\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Response Building\n364: \n365: The system SHALL build proper deletion responses.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Build single delete response\n368: - **GIVEN** a successful deletion of sandbox with:\n369:   - SessionID: `sess-abc-123`\n370:   - SandboxID: `sandbox-xyz-789`\n371:   - Resources cleaned: Pod, Service\n372: - **WHEN** building the response\n373: - **THEN** the response SHALL contain:\n374:   ```json\n375:   {\n376:     \"success\": true,\n377:     \"data\": {\n378:       \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-xyz-789\",\n379:       \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc-123\",\n380:       \"status\": \"deleted\",\n381:       \"deletedAt\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n382:       \"resourcesCleaned\": [\n383:         {\"kind\": \"Pod\", \"name\": \"sandbox-pod-xyz\", \"namespace\": \"default\"},\n384:         {\"kind\": \"Service\", \"name\": \"sandbox-svc-xyz\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}\n385:       ]\n386:     },\n387:     \"requestId\": \"req-uuid\",\n388:     \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\"\n389:   }\n390:   ```\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Build batch delete response\n393: - **GIVEN** a batch delete with mixed results\n394: - **WHEN** building the response\n395: - **THEN** the response SHALL contain separate arrays for deleted, failed, and notFound items\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ### Requirement: Context Propagation and Cancellation\n400: \n401: The system SHALL properly propagate context through the deletion flow.\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Pass context through deletion flow\n404: - **GIVEN** a request context with requestID and timeout\n405: - **WHEN** the deletion flow executes (validate → shutdown → cleanup → store delete)\n406: - **THEN** the context SHALL be passed to all operations for cancellation and timeout handling\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Handle client disconnect during deletion\n409: - **GIVEN** a deletion is in progress\n410: - **WHEN** the client disconnects (context cancelled)\n411: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n412:   1. Continue the deletion process (don't abort mid-way)\n413:   2. Log the client disconnect\n414:   3. Complete the cleanup\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: Timeout context for K8s operations\n417: - **GIVEN** a deletion involves K8s API calls\n418: - **WHEN** calling the dynamic client\n419: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `context.WithTimeout()` with appropriate deadline for each operation\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ### Requirement: Configuration\n424: \n425: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables.\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: Configure graceful timeout default\n428: - **GIVEN** environment variable `DEFAULT_GRACEFUL_TIMEOUT=60s`\n429: - **WHEN** no query parameter is provided\n430: - **THEN** the system SHALL use 60 seconds as default graceful timeout\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: Configure idle detection\n433: - **GIVEN** environment variables:\n434:   - `IDLE_DETECTION_ENABLED=true`\n435:   - `SANDBOX_IDLE_TIMEOUT=20m`\n436:   - `IDLE_SCAN_INTERVAL=2m`\n437:   - `IDLE_GRACE_PERIOD=3m`\n438: - **WHEN** the idle detector starts\n439: - **THEN** it SHALL use these values instead of defaults\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: Configure orphan detection\n442: - **GIVEN** environment variables:\n443:   - `ORPHAN_DETECTION_ENABLED=true`\n444:   - `ORPHAN_SCAN_INTERVAL=10m`\n445:   - `ORPHAN_MAX_AGE=2h`\n446: - **WHEN** the orphan detector starts\n447: - **THEN** it SHALL use these values\n448: \n449: ---\n450: \n451: ## File Index\n452: \n453: | Path | Purpose |\n454: |------|---------|\n455: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/delete.go` | HTTP handler for single sandbox deletion |\n456: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/batch.go` | HTTP handler for batch deletion |\n457: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/force.go` | HTTP handler for force deletion |\n458: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/manager.go` | `LifecycleManager` interface and orchestration |\n459: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/shutdown.go` | Graceful shutdown implementation |\n460: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/cleanup.go` | Resource cleanup implementation |\n461: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/state.go` | Lifecycle state machine |\n462: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/idle.go` | Idle timeout detector worker |\n463: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/orphan.go` | Orphan resource detector worker |\n464: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/types/lifecycle.go` | Lifecycle types and constants |\n465: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/routes.go` | Route registration for deletion endpoints |\n466: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/delete_test.go` | Handler unit tests |\n467: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/shutdown_test.go` | Shutdown flow tests |\n468: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/idle_test.go` | Idle detector tests |\n469: \n470: ---\n471: \n472: ## Dependencies\n473: \n474: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n475: |------------|---------|---------|\n476: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset, informers |\n477: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Dynamic client for Sandbox CR deletion |\n478: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery, deletion options |\n479: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Latest | HTTP framework (inherited from AR-004) |\n480: | `github.com/google/uuid` | Latest | UUID validation |\n481: | `github.com/go-redis/redis/v8` | Latest | Store operations for sandbox info |\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## API Endpoints Summary\n486: \n487: | Method | Path | Description |\n488: |--------|------|-------------|\n489: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n490: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n491: | DELETE | `/v1/sandboxes` | Batch delete sandboxes |\n492: | POST | `/v1/sandboxes/:sessionId/terminate` | Force terminate sandbox |\n493: | GET | `/v1/sandboxes/:sessionId/lifecycle` | Get lifecycle state |\n494: | GET | `/v1/sandboxes` | List sandboxes (with optional state filter) |\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ## Data Types\n499: \n500: ### DeleteSandboxRequest\n501: ```go\n502: type DeleteSandboxRequest struct {\n503:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n504: }\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ### DeleteSandboxResponse\n508: ```go\n509: type DeleteSandboxResponse struct {\n510:     SandboxID        string         `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n511:     SessionID        string         `json:\"sessionId\"`\n512:     Status           string         `json:\"status\"` // \"deleted\", \"terminating\", \"failed\"\n513:     DeletedAt        time.Time      `json:\"deletedAt,omitempty\"`\n514:     ResourcesCleaned []ResourceInfo `json:\"resourcesCleaned,omitempty\"`\n515: }\n516: \n517: type ResourceInfo struct {\n518:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n519:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n520:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n521: }\n522: ```\n523: \n524: ### BatchDeleteRequest\n525: ```go\n526: type BatchDeleteRequest struct {\n527:     SessionIDs []string `json:\"sessionIds\" validate:\"required,min=1,max=100\"`\n528: }\n529: ```\n530: \n531: ### BatchDeleteResponse\n532: ```go\n533: type BatchDeleteResponse struct {\n534:     Deleted  []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"deleted\"`\n535:     Failed   []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"failed\"`\n536:     NotFound []string            `json:\"notFound\"`\n537: }\n538: \n539: type BatchDeleteResult struct {\n540:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n541:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n542:     Error     string `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n543: }\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ### DeleteOptions\n547: ```go\n548: type DeleteOptions struct {\n549:     GracefulTimeout   time.Duration             `json:\"gracefulTimeout,omitempty\" default:\"30s\"`\n550:     Force             bool                      `json:\"force,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n551:     OrphanDependents  bool                      `json:\"orphanDependents,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n552:     PropagationPolicy *metav1.DeletionPropagation `json:\"propagationPolicy,omitempty\"`\n553: }\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ### LifecycleState\n557: ```go\n558: type LifecycleState string\n559: \n560: const (\n561:     StateRunning      LifecycleState = \"running\"\n562:     StateIdle         LifecycleState = \"idle\"\n563:     StateTerminating  LifecycleState = \"terminating\"\n564:     StateTerminated   LifecycleState = \"terminated\"\n565:     StateFailed       LifecycleState = \"failed\"\n566: )\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ### LifecycleStateResponse\n570: ```go\n571: type LifecycleStateResponse struct {\n572:     SessionID          string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n573:     SandboxID          string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n574:     CurrentState       LifecycleState     `json:\"currentState\"`\n575:     PreviousState      LifecycleState     `json:\"previousState,omitempty\"`\n576:     LastTransitionTime time.Time          `json:\"lastTransitionTime\"`\n577:     Reason             string             `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n578:     StateHistory       []StateTransition  `json:\"stateHistory,omitempty\"`\n579: }\n580: \n581: type StateTransition struct {\n582:     FromState LifecycleState `json:\"fromState\"`\n583:     ToState   LifecycleState `json:\"toState\"`\n584:     Timestamp time.Time      `json:\"timestamp\"`\n585:     Reason    string         `json:\"reason\"`\n586: }\n587: ```\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## Integration with client-go\n592: \n593: | Component | Usage |\n594: |-----------|-------|\n595: | `dynamic.Interface` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n596: | `metav1.DeleteOptions` | Configure graceful period, propagation policy |\n597: | `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Watch for resource changes during deletion |\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## Notes\n602: \n603: - Deletion is idempotent; deleting a non-existent sandbox returns 404, but force deleting returns 200 if already deleted\n604: - Graceful shutdown timeout can be customized per-request via query parameter or globally via environment variable\n605: - Background workers (idle detector, orphan cleaner) run independently and are resilient to individual operation failures\n606: - All K8s API errors are mapped to appropriate HTTP status codes following Kubernetes conventions\n607: - Store cleanup is attempted even if resource cleanup fails to prevent data inconsistency\n608: - Batch deletion processes sandboxes in parallel with a configurable concurrency limit (default: 10)\n\n(End of file - total 608 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-006  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management functionality for the WorkloadManager. This includes HTTP endpoints for deleting sandboxes (single, batch, force), graceful shutdown with configurable timeout, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan cleanup background workers. The implementation integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and extends the sandbox creation handler (AR-005).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Single Deletion Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to delete a single sandbox by its session ID.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete existing sandbox gracefully","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851063457,"end":1775851063473}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775851063508,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8c8b3001Wk6Wb2la9Ljlv0","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78f88d2e001ioUpSjRQWD8sZB","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":33846,"input":4,"output":226,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":2023,"read":31593}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775851067294,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8d79c001OpOYcuEThWLuxv","messageID":"msg_d78f8c8ed001zb1mie4OdOyM01","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851069495,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f8dbb000186ZbSRQ3kVc8tB","messageID":"msg_d78f8c8ed001zb1mie4OdOyM01","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-005  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime\n21: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with a valid pod template\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n24:   1. Validate the request (Kind=AgentRuntime, name and namespace non-empty)\n25:   2. Retrieve the AgentRuntime from informer cache\n26:   3. Build a Sandbox object with generated name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n27:   4. Create placeholder in Store with status \"pending\"\n28:   5. Register watcher before creating CR to avoid race conditions\n29:   6. Create the Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n30:   7. Wait up to 2 minutes for Sandbox to reach \"running\" status\n31:   8. Resolve Pod IP and build entryPoints from spec.Ports\n32:   9. Update Store with full SandboxInfo including entryPoints\n33:   10. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing sessionId and entryPoints\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing pod template\n36: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `invalid-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with `spec.template=nil`\n37: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"invalid-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message containing \"pod template\"\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent AgentRuntime\n41: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `missing-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n42: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"agent runtime not found\"\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with invalid request body\n46: - **GIVEN** a malformed JSON payload\n47: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with invalid JSON\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing required fields\n51: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `name` field\n52: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n53: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"name is required\"\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing namespace\n56: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `namespace` field\n57: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\"}`\n58: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"namespace is required\"\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n63: \n64: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from CodeInterpreter workload definitions.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid CodeInterpreter\n67: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default` with valid template\n68: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"test-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n69: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n70:   1. Validate the request (Kind=CodeInterpreter, name and namespace non-empty)\n71:   2. Retrieve the CodeInterpreter from informer cache\n72:   3. Build a Sandbox or SandboxClaim object based on WarmPoolSize\n73:   4. Apply default ports `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if spec.Ports is empty\n74:   5. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey is available\n75:   6. Follow the same creation and wait flow as AgentRuntime\n76:   7. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Create SandboxClaim for warm pool\n79: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `warm-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n80: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n81: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a `SandboxClaim` (not full Sandbox) with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Create full Sandbox for non-warm pool\n84: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `cold-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize=0` or unset\n85: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n86: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a full `Sandbox` with single container named `code-interpreter`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n89: - **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter named `missing-interpreter` exists\n90: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"code interpreter not found\"\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Sandbox Object Building\n96: \n97: The system SHALL build proper Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload definitions.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Build Sandbox object with correct metadata\n100: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with name `my-runtime` and a sessionID `sess-123`\n101: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n102: - **THEN** the resulting Sandbox SHALL have:\n103:   - Name: `my-runtime-{8-char-random}`\n104:   - APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n105:   - Kind: `Sandbox`\n106:   - Labels:\n107:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`: sessionID\n108:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`: runtime.Name\n109:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name`: sandboxName\n110:     - `managed-by`: `agentcube-workload-manager`\n111:   - Annotations:\n112:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`: SessionTimeout (default \"15m\")\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Build Sandbox with lifecycle settings\n115: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration` set to 8 hours\n116: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n117: - **THEN** the Sandbox spec SHALL include `lifecycle.shutdownTime` set to `now + MaxSessionDuration`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox with auth mode\n120: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=picod` and a public key available\n121: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n122: - **THEN** the container SHALL have environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` set to the public key\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox without auth\n125: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=none`\n126: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n127: - **THEN** the container SHALL NOT have `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Build SandboxClaim for warm pool\n130: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n131: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxClaimObject()` is called\n132: - **THEN** the resulting object SHALL have:\n133:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n134:   - Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n135:   - Minimal metadata (no full PodSpec)\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Sandbox Creation and Wait Flow\n140: \n141: The system SHALL orchestrate the creation flow with proper synchronization and timeouts.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Register watcher before CR creation\n144: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n145: - **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n146: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `WatchSandboxOnce()` to register the watcher BEFORE calling `dynamicClient.Create()`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Store placeholder before CR creation\n149: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n150: - **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `StoreSandbox()` with status \"pending\" BEFORE creating the CR\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Successfully wait for sandbox running\n154: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created\n155: - **WHEN** the SandboxReconciler notifies the sandbox is running within 2 minutes\n156: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n157:   1. Receive notification from the watcher channel\n158:   2. Resolve Pod IP using `resolvePodIP()`\n159:   3. Build entryPoints from ports and Pod IP\n160:   4. Update Store with status \"running\" and entryPoints\n161:   5. Return the complete SandboxInfo\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Timeout waiting for sandbox running\n164: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created but does not reach running state\n165: - **WHEN** 2 minutes elapse without receiving running notification\n166: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n167:   1. Cancel the wait context\n168:   2. Delete the CR with a 30-second timeout context\n169:   3. Delete the Store placeholder\n170:   4. Return error \"sandbox creation timed out\"\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from annotation\n173: - **GIVEN** a running Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name=my-pod`\n174: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL first check the annotation and use `my-pod` as the pod name to look up\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from owner reference\n178: - **GIVEN** a running Sandbox without pod name annotation\n179: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n180: - **THEN** the system SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` and select the one with OwnerReference matching the Sandbox\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution failure\n183: - **GIVEN** no running pod exists for the sandbox\n184: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n185: - **THEN** the system SHALL return error \"no running pod found for sandbox {name}\"\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Rollback and Cleanup\n190: \n191: The system SHALL implement proper rollback on creation failures.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Rollback on CR creation failure\n194: - **GIVEN** Store placeholder has been created\n195: - **WHEN** dynamic client Create() fails\n196: - **THEN** the system SHALL delete the Store placeholder using `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Rollback on timeout\n199: - **GIVEN** CR has been created but sandbox never reaches running\n200: - **WHEN** timeout occurs after 2 minutes\n201: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n202:   1. Delete the CR using dynamic client with 30s timeout\n203:   2. Delete the Store placeholder\n204:   3. Return timeout error\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Rollback on Pod IP resolution failure\n207: - **GIVEN** CR has been created and sandbox is running\n208: - **WHEN** Pod IP resolution fails\n209: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n210:   1. Delete the CR\n211:   2. Delete the Store placeholder\n212:   3. Return resolution error\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Handle Store update failure\n215: - **GIVEN** CR is created and running, Pod IP is resolved\n216: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox()` fails\n217: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n218:   1. Log warning about Store inconsistency\n219:   2. CR will be eventually cleaned up by GC\n220:   3. Return the error\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Request Validation\n225: \n226: The system SHALL validate CreateSandboxRequest according to defined rules.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Validate valid request\n229: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"AgentRuntime\"`, `Name=\"test\"`, `Namespace=\"default\"`\n230: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n231: - **THEN** the method SHALL return nil (no error)\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Validate rejects empty name\n234: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Name` field\n235: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n236: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"name is required\"\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Validate rejects empty namespace\n239: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Namespace` field\n240: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n241: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"namespace is required\"\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Validate rejects invalid kind\n244: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n245: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n246: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"kind is required\" (or invalid kind)\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Response Building\n251: \n252: The system SHALL build proper CreateSandboxResponse from SandboxInfo.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Build response with entryPoints\n255: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with:\n256:   - SessionID: `sess-abc-123`\n257:   - SandboxID: `runtime-xyz-789`\n258:   - SandboxName: `my-runtime-abcdef12`\n259:   - EntryPoints: `[{Path: \"/\", Protocol: \"HTTP\", Endpoint: \"10.244.0.5:8080\"}]`\n260: - **WHEN** building the HTTP response\n261: - **THEN** the response SHALL contain:\n262:   ```json\n263:   {\n264:     \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc-123\",\n265:     \"sandboxId\": \"runtime-xyz-789\",\n266:     \"sandboxName\": \"my-runtime-abcdef12\",\n267:     \"entryPoints\": [\n268:       {\n269:         \"path\": \"/\",\n270:         \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n271:         \"endpoint\": \"10.244.0.5:8080\"\n272:       }\n273:     ]\n274:   }\n275:   ```\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Authentication Integration\n280: \n281: The system SHALL integrate with authentication middleware when enabled.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Extract auth context when auth enabled\n284: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has valid Authorization header\n285: - **WHEN** the handler processes the request\n286: - **THEN** the context SHALL contain:\n287:   - `contextKeyUserToken`: the bearer token\n288:   - `contextKeyServiceAccount`: the service account name\n289:   - `contextKeyNamespace`: the namespace for per-user client caching\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Reject request without auth header\n292: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has no Authorization header\n293: - **WHEN** authMiddleware processes the request\n294: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with message \"Missing authorization header\"\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: Reject invalid token\n297: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has invalid token\n298: - **WHEN** authMiddleware calls TokenReview\n299: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with TokenReview error message\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Use per-user client when auth enabled\n302: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and auth context is present\n303: - **WHEN** creating the Sandbox CR\n304: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` to get per-user dynamic client\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ### Requirement: Idempotency\n309: \n310: The system SHALL support idempotent creation requests.\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Return existing session for duplicate request\n313: - **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime` has already succeeded with sessionID `sess-123`\n314: - **WHEN** the same request is made again\n315: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n316:   1. Check Store for existing session by workload name\n317:   2. Return the existing sessionID without creating new sandbox\n318:   3. Return HTTP 200 with original CreateSandboxResponse\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ### Requirement: Error Handling and HTTP Status Mapping\n323: \n324: The system SHALL map internal errors to appropriate HTTP status codes.\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: Map JSON binding error to 400\n327: - **GIVEN** request body is malformed JSON\n328: - **WHEN** `c.ShouldBindJSON()` fails\n329: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Map validation error to 400\n332: - **GIVEN** request fails validation (missing required field)\n333: - **WHEN** `Validate()` returns error\n334: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with validation error message\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Map not found to 404\n337: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is not found in informer cache\n338: - **WHEN** lookup fails\n339: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with appropriate \"not found\" message\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Map internal errors to 500\n342: - **GIVEN** an unexpected internal error occurs (Store failure, K8s API error)\n343: - **WHEN** error is processed\n344: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\" (details logged but not exposed)\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Map timeout to 500\n347: - **GIVEN** sandbox creation times out after 2 minutes\n348: - **WHEN** timeout occurs\n349: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\"\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Context Propagation\n354: \n355: The system SHALL properly propagate context through the creation flow.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Pass context through creation flow\n358: - **GIVEN** a request context with requestID and auth info\n359: - **WHEN** the creation flow executes (validate → build → create → wait)\n360: - **THEN** the context SHALL be passed to all operations for cancellation and timeout handling\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Handle context cancellation during wait\n363: - **GIVEN** sandbox is waiting for running status\n364: - **WHEN** the parent context is cancelled (e.g., client disconnects)\n365: - **THEN** the wait SHALL be cancelled and resources cleaned up\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ### Requirement: Timeout Configuration\n370: \n371: The system SHALL enforce configurable timeouts for sandbox operations.\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Enforce 2-minute creation timeout\n374: - **GIVEN** default timeout configuration\n375: - **WHEN** creating sandbox with `context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)`\n376: - **THEN** the operation SHALL timeout after 2 minutes if sandbox doesn't reach running\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Enforce 30-second deletion timeout on rollback\n379: - **GIVEN** rollback is triggered after creation timeout\n380: - **WHEN** deleting the CR\n381: - **THEN** the deletion SHALL use `context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)`\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## File Index\n386: \n387: | Path | Purpose |\n388: |------|---------|\n389: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n390: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | `sandboxCreator` struct and `createSandbox()` orchestration |\n391: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | `buildSandboxObject()`, `buildSandboxClaimObject()`, `resolvePodIP()`, `buildEntryPoints()` |\n392: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce()`, sandbox status tracking |\n393: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | GVR definitions, `Informers` struct, informer lifecycle |\n394: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | `K8sClient`, `ClientCache`, `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` |\n395: | `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go` | `authMiddleware`, context keys, token validation |\n396: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, label/annotation keys |\n397: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox.go` | Sandbox domain types (if not in pkg/apis) |\n398: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` | Handler unit tests |\n399: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` | Sandbox creation flow tests |\n400: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` | Object building tests |\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Dependencies\n405: \n406: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n407: |------------|---------|---------|\n408: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset, informers, listers |\n409: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Dynamic client, REST client |\n410: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery, unstructured |\n411: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Latest | HTTP framework (inherited from AR-004) |\n412: | `github.com/google/uuid` | Latest | UUID generation for sessionID |\n413: | `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | Latest | Test dependency for mock Redis |\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## API Endpoints Summary\n418: \n419: | Method | Path | Description |\n420: |--------|------|-------------|\n421: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime definition |\n422: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter definition |\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## Data Types\n427: \n428: ### CreateSandboxRequest\n429: ```go\n430: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n431:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n432:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n433:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n434: }\n435: ```\n436: \n437: ### CreateSandboxResponse\n438: ```go\n439: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n440:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n441:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n442:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n443:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n444: }\n445: \n446: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n447:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // route path prefix\n448:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n449:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n450: }\n451: ```\n452: \n453: ### SandboxInfo (Store model)\n454: ```go\n455: type SandboxInfo struct {\n456:     Kind             string                `json:\"kind\"`             // \"Sandbox\" or \"SandboxClaim\"\n457:     SandboxID        string                `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n458:     SandboxNamespace string                `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n459:     Name             string                `json:\"name\"`\n460:     SessionID        string                `json:\"sessionId\"`\n461:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint   `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n462:     Status           string                `json:\"status\"`           // \"pending\", \"running\", \"failed\"\n463:     CreatedAt        time.Time             `json:\"createdAt\"`\n464:     ExpiresAt        time.Time             `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n465: }\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Integration with client-go\n471: \n472: | Component | Usage |\n473: |-----------|-------|\n474: | `clientset/versioned.Interface` | Get typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n475: | `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Informer lifecycle management |\n476: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister` | Read-only AgentRuntime queries |\n477: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister` | Read-only CodeInterpreter queries |\n478: | `fake.Clientset` | Unit test mocks |\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## Notes\n483: \n484: - Watcher MUST be registered BEFORE creating the CR to avoid race conditions where Sandbox enters running before watcher is ready\n485: - Store placeholder MUST be created BEFORE CR creation for idempotency and rollback\n486: - Dynamic client is used for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs (external to agentcube)\n487: - Per-user K8s client is used when authentication is enabled\n488: - All timeouts are configurable via constants in `defaults.go`\n489: - EntryPoints are built from `spec.Ports` with format: `{PathPrefix, Protocol, PodIP:Port}`\n\n(End of file - total 489 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-005  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851069474,"end":1775851069492}}}}
