{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851365355,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78f94eca0013pNtizLQ6E3UxX","messageID":"msg_d78f8e061001s7TrW6BdXl5BIO","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n\n#### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers\n- **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes configuration and WorkloadManager configuration\n- **WHEN** the operator calls `controllerManager.Start(ctx)`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Create a new controller-runtime manager with the provided configuration\n  2. Register the AgentRuntimeReconciler with the manager\n  3. Register the CodeInterpreterReconciler with the manager\n  4. Start all controllers in separate goroutines\n  5. Block until context cancellation or error\n\n#### Scenario: Controller manager uses in-cluster config\n- **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n- **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to get in-cluster configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Controller manager uses kubeconfig\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n- **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n\n#### Scenario: Controller manager shuts down gracefully\n- **GIVEN** the controller manager is running with active reconciliations\n- **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Stop accepting new reconciliation requests\n  2. Wait for in-progress reconciliations to complete (up to graceful timeout)\n  3. Stop all watches and release resources\n  4. Return without error\n\n#### Scenario: Controller manager health check\n- **GIVEN** the controller manager is running\n- **WHEN** the `/readyz` endpoint is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return ready only when all controllers are started and caches are synced\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n\nThe system SHALL implement a reconciler for AgentRuntime resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile new AgentRuntime creation\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `new-runtime` is created in namespace `default`\n- **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Fetch the AgentRuntime object from the API server\n  2. Set initial status phase to `Pending`\n  3. Add finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n  4. Create the underlying sandbox Pod\n  5. Set OwnerReference on the Pod pointing to the AgentRuntime\n  6. Update status with `SandboxCreated` condition set to `True`\n  7. Requeue after 5 seconds to check sandbox status\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox running\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Running` phase\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Check the Pod status via API server\n  2. Update AgentRuntime status phase to `Running`\n  3. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n  4. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n  5. Update `Status.PodIP` with the pod's IP address\n  6. Update `Status.SandboxID` with the pod's UID\n  7. Update `Status.StartTime` with the pod's start time\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox failure\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Failed` phase\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Update status phase to `Failed`\n  2. Set `Failed` condition to `True` with reason and message\n  3. Set `Ready` condition to `False`\n  4. Record the failure reason in `Status.Reason`\n  5. Record error message in `Status.Message`\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime spec update\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with generation `2` and observedGeneration `1`\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Detect the spec change (generation != observedGeneration)\n  2. Set phase to `Pending` during update\n  3. Apply the new spec to the sandbox resources\n  4. Update `Status.ObservedGeneration` to match generation\n  5. Requeue to monitor the update progress\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime with finalizer on deletion\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp set and finalizer present\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Set phase to `Pending` (terminating state)\n  2. Delete the associated sandbox Pod\n  3. Delete any associated Services or Ingress resources\n  4. Remove the finalizer from the AgentRuntime\n  5. Allow Kubernetes to garbage collect the AgentRuntime\n\n#### Scenario: Handle AgentRuntime not found\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for an AgentRuntime that no longer exists\n- **WHEN** the reconciler fetches the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL return without error (object was deleted)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n\nThe system SHALL implement a reconciler for CodeInterpreter resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile new CodeInterpreter creation\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `new-interpreter` is created in namespace `default`\n- **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Fetch the CodeInterpreter object from the API server\n  2. Set initial `Ready` status to `false`\n  3. Add finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n  4. Create the sandbox Pod from `spec.template`\n  5. Configure ports from `spec.ports`\n  6. Set OwnerReference on created resources\n  7. Add `SandboxCreated` condition with status `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter with warm pool\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.warmPoolSize > 0`\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Create a SandboxClaim instead of direct Sandbox\n  2. Set `SandboxClaimCreated` condition\n  3. Monitor the SandboxClaim status\n  4. Update CodeInterpreter status when sandbox is assigned\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter ready state\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a running sandbox Pod\n- **WHEN** the pod passes readiness checks\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Set `Status.Ready` to `true`\n  2. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n  3. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n  4. Record the ready transition timestamp\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter auth configuration\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.authMode=picod`\n- **WHEN** the reconciler creates the sandbox\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n  2. Configure authentication sidecar if required\n  3. Set appropriate labels for auth routing\n\n#### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter deletion\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with deletion timestamp set\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Release warm pool sandboxes if applicable\n  2. Delete the SandboxClaim or Sandbox\n  3. Clean up associated resources\n  4. Remove the finalizer\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Event-Driven Watch and Reconciliation\n\nThe system SHALL use informers to watch for resource changes and trigger reconciliation.\n\n#### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime events\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime reconciler is running\n- **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, or deleted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Receive the event from the API server watch stream\n  2. Map the event to a reconciliation request\n  3. Add the request to the work queue\n  4. Wake up a worker to process the request\n\n#### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n- **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter reconciler is running\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter resource changes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation request for that resource\n\n#### Scenario: Watch owned Pod events\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has created a sandbox Pod\n- **WHEN** the Pod status changes (e.g., transitions to Running)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Map the Pod event to its owning AgentRuntime\n  2. Enqueue a reconciliation request for the AgentRuntime\n  3. Trigger status update based on Pod state\n\n#### Scenario: Watch owned Service events\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter has created a Service\n- **WHEN** the Service endpoints are updated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation for the owning CodeInterpreter\n\n#### Scenario: Handle watch reconnection\n- **GIVEN** the API server watch connection is lost\n- **WHEN** the connection drops\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Log the disconnection event\n  2. Attempt to reconnect with exponential backoff\n  3. Resync the cache on reconnection\n  4. Continue processing without data loss\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Reconcile Queue with Rate Limiting\n\nThe system SHALL implement a work queue with rate limiting for reconciliation requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Add request to queue\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime`\n- **WHEN** the request is enqueued\n- **THEN** the system SHALL add it to the work queue with the resource namespace and name\n\n#### Scenario: Process request from queue\n- **GIVEN** a worker is available and a request is in the queue\n- **WHEN** the worker dequeues the request\n- **THEN** it SHALL call the appropriate reconciler's `Reconcile()` method\n\n#### Scenario: Rate limit failed reconciliations\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a retryable error\n- **WHEN** the error is returned\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Increment the retry counter for the resource\n  2. Calculate backoff delay using exponential backoff (base 5ms, max 1000s)\n  3. Re-add the request to the queue with the calculated delay\n  4. Not block other reconciliations\n\n#### Scenario: Max retries exceeded\n- **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation 5 times\n- **WHEN** the max retry limit is reached\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Drop the request from the queue\n  2. Update the resource status with `Failed` condition\n  3. Record the permanent failure in status\n  4. Log the error for operator investigation\n\n#### Scenario: Successful reconciliation resets rate limit\n- **GIVEN** a resource that previously failed reconciliation\n- **WHEN** the reconciliation succeeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL reset the retry counter for that resource to zero\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent workers process queue\n- **GIVEN** the controller is configured with 3 concurrent workers\n- **WHEN** multiple requests are in the queue\n- **THEN** the system SHALL process up to 3 reconciliations concurrently\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Exponential Backoff for Failures\n\nThe system SHALL implement exponential backoff for transient failures.\n\n#### Scenario: Calculate backoff delay\n- **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation `n` times\n- **WHEN** calculating the next retry delay\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the formula: `min(base * 2^n, max)` where base=5ms, max=1000s\n\n#### Scenario: Apply jitter to backoff\n- **GIVEN** a calculated backoff of 10 seconds\n- **WHEN** scheduling the retry\n- **THEN** the system SHALL add ±10% jitter to prevent thundering herd\n\n#### Scenario: Reset backoff on success\n- **GIVEN** a resource with accumulated backoff delay\n- **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL reset the backoff to the base value\n\n#### Scenario: Skip backoff for non-retryable errors\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a non-retryable error (e.g., invalid spec)\n- **WHEN** the error is returned\n- **THEN** the system SHALL not retry and update status with permanent failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Finalizer Handling\n\nThe system SHALL implement finalizers for graceful resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n- **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime resource without finalizers\n- **WHEN** the reconciler first processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL add the finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n\n#### Scenario: Execute finalizer on deletion\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n- **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Check if deletion timestamp is set\n  2. Execute cleanup logic (delete pods, services)\n  3. Remove the finalizer from the resource\n  4. Return to allow Kubernetes deletion\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple finalizers handling\n- **GIVEN** a resource with multiple finalizers including the controller's finalizer\n- **WHEN** processing deletion\n- **THEN** the system SHALL only remove its own finalizer and preserve others\n\n#### Scenario: Finalizer cleanup failure\n- **GIVEN** cleanup fails during finalizer execution (e.g., API server error)\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Not remove the finalizer\n  2. Return the error to trigger retry\n  3. Keep the resource in terminating state\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter finalizer\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter resource\n- **WHEN** processed by the reconciler\n- **THEN** it SHALL use finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status Updates and Condition Management\n\nThe system SHALL properly manage resource status and conditions.\n\n#### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime reconciliation determines new state\n- **WHEN** updating status\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Use the status subresource update (`UpdateStatus`)\n  2. Set appropriate phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n  3. Update conditions with proper transition timestamps\n  4. Preserve existing conditions not being modified\n\n#### Scenario: Add new condition\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime without a `SandboxCreated` condition\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Append a new `AgentRuntimeCondition` to the conditions array\n  2. Set `Type`, `Status`, `LastTransitionTime`, `Reason`, and `Message`\n  3. Use strategic merge patch to avoid conflicts\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing condition\n- **GIVEN** an existing condition with status `False`\n- **WHEN** the condition status changes to `True`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Update the `Status` field\n  2. Update `LastTransitionTime` to now\n  3. Update `Reason` and `Message` if provided\n\n#### Scenario: Observed generation tracking\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `metadata.generation=5`\n- **WHEN** spec reconciliation completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.observedGeneration=5`\n\n#### Scenario: Handle status update conflict\n- **GIVEN** a status update fails with conflict error\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Fetch the latest resource version\n  2. Re-apply the status changes\n  3. Retry the update (up to 3 times)\n\n#### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter ready status\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with running sandbox\n- **WHEN** all readiness checks pass\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.ready=true` and update conditions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: OwnerReference Management\n\nThe system SHALL set OwnerReferences on created resources for garbage collection.\n\n#### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Pod\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime creates a sandbox Pod\n- **WHEN** creating the Pod\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set:\n  ```yaml\n  ownerReferences:\n  - apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n    kind: AgentRuntime\n    name: <agentruntime-name>\n    uid: <agentruntime-uid>\n    controller: true\n    blockOwnerDeletion: true\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Service\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a Service\n- **WHEN** creating the Service\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference pointing to the CodeInterpreter\n\n#### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on ConfigMap\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a ConfigMap for configuration\n- **WHEN** creating the ConfigMap\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference for automatic cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: Cascade deletion with OwnerReference\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with OwnerReference-set Pods\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is deleted\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL automatically garbage collect the owned Pods\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration with WorkloadManager Service Layer\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP service.\n\n#### Scenario: Reconciler updates Store via service layer\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation updates sandbox status\n- **WHEN** status changes from `Pending` to `Running`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call the service layer to update the Store entry\n\n#### Scenario: Service layer triggers reconciliation\n- **GIVEN** an HTTP request modifies an AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** the modification is applied via Kubernetes API\n- **THEN** the watch SHALL trigger reconciliation\n\n#### Scenario: Reconciler reads from informer cache\n- **GIVEN** the reconciler needs to list related resources\n- **WHEN** querying resources\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the informer cache for efficiency, falling back to API server on cache miss\n\n#### Scenario: Shared informer factory\n- **GIVEN** both reconcilers and HTTP handlers need resource information\n- **WHEN** initializing the system\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use a shared informer factory to avoid duplicate watches\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n\nThe system SHALL expose metrics for reconciliation operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Expose reconcile latency metric\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation completes\n- **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n- **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_latency_seconds` histogram with labels:\n  - `controller` (agentruntime/codeinterpreter)\n  - `result` (success/error)\n\n#### Scenario: Expose reconcile count metric\n- **GIVEN** reconciliations are being processed\n- **WHEN** metrics are collected\n- **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_total` counter with labels:\n  - `controller`\n  - `result`\n\n#### Scenario: Expose queue depth metric\n- **GIVEN** the work queue has pending items\n- **WHEN** metrics are collected\n- **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_queue_depth` gauge per controller\n\n#### Scenario: Expose retry count metric\n- **GIVEN** resources are being retried\n- **WHEN** metrics are collected\n- **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_retries_total` counter\n\n#### Scenario: Structured logging for reconciliation\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation is processed\n- **WHEN** logging\n- **THEN** the system SHALL include fields:\n  - `controller`\n  - `resource_name`\n  - `resource_namespace`\n  - `operation` (create/update/delete)\n  - `duration_ms`\n  - `result`\n\n#### Scenario: Log reconciliation errors\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails\n- **WHEN** logging the error\n- **THEN** the system SHALL include:\n  - Error message\n  - Stack trace (if available)\n  - Resource details\n  - Retry count\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling and Recovery\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully and recover when possible.\n\n#### Scenario: Handle API server unavailable\n- **GIVEN** the Kubernetes API server is temporarily unavailable\n- **WHEN** the reconciler tries to fetch/update a resource\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Log the error\n  2. Return a retryable error\n  3. Requeue with exponential backoff\n\n#### Scenario: Handle network timeout\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call times out\n- **WHEN** the timeout occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as retryable and requeue\n\n#### Scenario: Handle RBAC permission denied\n- **GIVEN** the controller lacks permissions for an operation\n- **WHEN** a forbidden error occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Log the error with details\n  2. Not retry (non-retryable)\n  3. Update resource status with failure\n\n#### Scenario: Handle invalid resource spec\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has an invalid spec\n- **WHEN** reconciliation fails validation\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Update status with `Failed` condition\n  2. Record validation error in status\n  3. Not retry\n\n#### Scenario: Recover from panic\n- **GIVEN** a reconciler panics during execution\n- **WHEN** the panic occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Recover from the panic\n  2. Log the panic with stack trace\n  3. Update metrics\n  4. Continue processing other resources\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Leader Election (Preparation)\n\nThe system SHALL prepare for leader election to support HA deployments.\n\n#### Scenario: Configure leader election options\n- **GIVEN** the controller manager initializes\n- **WHEN** setting up the manager\n- **THEN** it SHALL accept leader election configuration (disabled by default in this AR)\n\n#### Scenario: Skip leader election in single-replica mode\n- **GIVEN** leader election is not enabled\n- **WHEN** the controller starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL start immediately without acquiring a lease\n\n#### Scenario: Leader election resource naming\n- **GIVEN** leader election is configured\n- **WHEN** acquiring the lease\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the lease name `agentcube-workload-manager-leader-election`\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/manager.go` | Controller manager bootstrap and lifecycle |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller.go` | AgentRuntimeReconciler implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller.go` | CodeInterpreterReconciler implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | Base reconciler interface and utilities |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | Finalizer helper functions |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/conditions.go` | Condition management utilities |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ownerref.go` | OwnerReference helper functions |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | Prometheus metrics definitions |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/watch.go` | Watch event handlers and mappers |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ratelimiter.go` | Rate limiter configuration |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/controller.go` | Controller command entry point |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller_test.go` | AgentRuntime reconciler tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller_test.go` | CodeInterpreter reconciler tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/suite_test.go` | Controller test suite setup |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.20.0+` | Controller runtime framework |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated clientset and informers |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics |\n| `github.com/go-logr/logr` | Latest | Structured logging |\n\n---\n\n## API Integration\n\n| Component | Usage |\n|-----------|-------|\n| `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` | Resource type being reconciled |\n| `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` | Resource type being reconciled |\n| `client-go/informers` | Watch resource changes |\n| `client-go/listers` | Cached resource reads |\n| `controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Controller-runtime client |\n| `controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile` | Reconcile interface |\n| `controller-runtime/pkg/controller` | Controller builder |\n| `controller-runtime/pkg/manager` | Manager interface |\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n### Reconciler Configuration\n```go\ntype ReconcilerConfig struct {\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int           // default: 3\n    RateLimiterBaseDelay    time.Duration // default: 5ms\n    RateLimiterMaxDelay     time.Duration // default: 1000s\n    MaxRetries              int           // default: 5\n    GracefulShutdownTimeout time.Duration // default: 30s\n}\n```\n\n### Reconcile Result\n```go\ntype ReconcileResult struct {\n    Requeue      bool\n    RequeueAfter time.Duration\n    Error        error\n}\n```\n\n### Finalizer Constants\n```go\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeFinalizer    = \"agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n    CodeInterpreterFinalizer = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Metrics Reference\n\n| Metric Name | Type | Labels | Description |\n|-------------|------|--------|-------------|\n| `reconcile_latency_seconds` | Histogram | controller, result | Reconciliation duration |\n| `reconcile_total` | Counter | controller, result | Total reconciliations |\n| `reconcile_queue_depth` | Gauge | controller | Current queue depth |\n| `reconcile_retries_total` | Counter | controller | Total retries |\n| `resource_status_phase` | Gauge | controller, phase | Resources by phase |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The reconciler uses controller-runtime for efficient resource watching and reconciliation\n- Rate limiting prevents thundering herd on API server errors\n- Finalizers ensure cleanup before resource deletion\n- OwnerReferences enable Kubernetes garbage collection\n- Status updates use the subresource to avoid spec conflicts\n- The controller integrates with existing WorkloadManager HTTP service\n- Metrics are exposed via the same `/metrics` endpoint as the HTTP service\n- Leader election is prepared but not required for single-replica deployments\n- All controllers share a single manager and informer cache for efficiency\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851365342,"end":1775851365352}}}}
