{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851372675,"sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","part":{"id":"prt_d78fd7b940013h5H67nXBR9UqU","messageID":"msg_d78fd6433001a56neCHainNVgQ","sessionID":"ses_287080b2cfferkvBPF2P0Q3FTV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-007  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** L  \n9: \n10: Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes configuration and WorkloadManager configuration\n22: - **WHEN** the operator calls `controllerManager.Start(ctx)`\n23: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n24:   1. Create a new controller-runtime manager with the provided configuration\n25:   2. Register the AgentRuntimeReconciler with the manager\n26:   3. Register the CodeInterpreterReconciler with the manager\n27:   4. Start all controllers in separate goroutines\n28:   5. Block until context cancellation or error\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses in-cluster config\n31: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n32: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL use `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to get in-cluster configuration\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses kubeconfig\n36: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n37: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Controller manager shuts down gracefully\n41: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running with active reconciliations\n42: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n44:   1. Stop accepting new reconciliation requests\n45:   2. Wait for in-progress reconciliations to complete (up to graceful timeout)\n46:   3. Stop all watches and release resources\n47:   4. Return without error\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Controller manager health check\n50: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running\n51: - **WHEN** the `/readyz` endpoint is called\n52: - **THEN** it SHALL return ready only when all controllers are started and caches are synced\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n57: \n58: The system SHALL implement a reconciler for AgentRuntime resources.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Reconcile new AgentRuntime creation\n61: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `new-runtime` is created in namespace `default`\n62: - **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n64:   1. Fetch the AgentRuntime object from the API server\n65:   2. Set initial status phase to `Pending`\n66:   3. Add finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n67:   4. Create the underlying sandbox Pod\n68:   5. Set OwnerReference on the Pod pointing to the AgentRuntime\n69:   6. Update status with `SandboxCreated` condition set to `True`\n70:   7. Requeue after 5 seconds to check sandbox status\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox running\n73: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Running` phase\n74: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n75: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n76:   1. Check the Pod status via API server\n77:   2. Update AgentRuntime status phase to `Running`\n78:   3. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n79:   4. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n80:   5. Update `Status.PodIP` with the pod's IP address\n81:   6. Update `Status.SandboxID` with the pod's UID\n82:   7. Update `Status.StartTime` with the pod's start time\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox failure\n85: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Failed` phase\n86: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n88:   1. Update status phase to `Failed`\n89:   2. Set `Failed` condition to `True` with reason and message\n90:   3. Set `Ready` condition to `False`\n91:   4. Record the failure reason in `Status.Reason`\n92:   5. Record error message in `Status.Message`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime spec update\n95: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with generation `2` and observedGeneration `1`\n96: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Detect the spec change (generation != observedGeneration)\n99:   2. Set phase to `Pending` during update\n100:   3. Apply the new spec to the sandbox resources\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 652. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n\n#### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851372658,"end":1775851372673}}}}
