s |\n638: | `resource_status_phase` | Gauge | controller, phase | Resources by phase |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Notes\n643: \n644: - The reconciler uses controller-runtime for efficient resource watching and reconciliation\n645: - Rate limiting prevents thundering herd on API server errors\n646: - Finalizers ensure cleanup before resource deletion\n647: - OwnerReferences enable Kubernetes garbage collection\n648: - Status updates use the subresource to avoid spec conflicts\n649: - The controller integrates with existing WorkloadManager HTTP service\n650: - Metrics are exposed via the same `/metrics` endpoint as the HTTP service\n651: - Leader election is prepared but not required for single-replica deployments\n652: - All controllers share a single manager and informer cache for efficiency\n\n(End of file - total 652 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### Reconciler Configuration\n```go\ntype ReconcilerConfig struct {\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int           // default: 3\n    RateLimiterBaseDelay    time.Duration // default: 5ms\n    RateLimiterMaxDelay     time.Duration // default: 1000s\n    MaxRetries              int           // default: 5\n    GracefulShutdownTimeout time.Duration // default: 30s\n}\n```\n\n### Reconcile Result\n```go\ntype ReconcileResult struct {\n    Requeue      bool\n    RequeueAfter time.Duration\n    Error        error\n}\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851397016,"end":1775851397025}}}}
